[SN]TITLE[SN]
Coleraine: Man charged with attempted murder

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with attempted murder after a man in his 50s was critically injured in an attack in Coleraine, County Londonderry.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The victim was seriously assaulted outside a house in Ballycastle Road in the town at about 01:00 BST on Monday.
The accused, who is 35, is due to appear at Coleraine Magistrates' Court next month.
The victim remains in a critical condition at the Royal Victoria Hospital in Belfast.
